==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dormy
<hw>Dor"my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Origin
uncertain.]</ety> <fld>(Golf)</fld> <def>Up, or ahead, as many holes as
remain to be played; -- said of a player or side.</def></p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A player who is <xex>dormy</xex> can not be beaten, and
at the worst must halve the match. <rj><au>Encyc. of
Sport.</au></rj></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dorn</ent>⟦br⟧
